<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    Expressions Editor</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>The Expressions Editor is responsible for maintaining and moderating the introductions/farewells forums. <br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    Guilds Editor</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>The Guild Directory Editor is responsible for maintaining and moderating the guilds forums. The primary concern should be maintaining an accurate list of MM guilds and forums.<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    Commerce Editor</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>The Commerce Editor is responsible for maintaining and moderating the trade forums, and pruning them when necessary.<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    Polls Editor</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>The Opinion Polls Editor is responsible for mainting and moderating the polls forums. His primary duty is to lock old polls (so they are not bumped repeatedly) and provide fresh new polls on a daily basis to attract new visitors and encourage discussion.<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    RP Editor</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>The roleplaying editor is responsible for hosting and moderating the roleplay board, which also serves as a frontpage to the MMRP organization.<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    Science Editor</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>The science editor is responsible for hosting and moderating the science/sci-fi board and posting relevant news from the real world. <br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    HTML Editor</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>The HTML staffperson, along with the primary admins, is responsible for implementing various coding and bells and whistles to make the site both easily navigable and appealing.<br><br>** Additional staff is added as needed. If you would like to volunteer your talents, please contact: Destructis - <!--EZCODE MAIL START--><a href="mailto: Destructis@hotmail.com"> Destructis@hotmail.com</a><!--EZCODE MAIL END--> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub18.ezboard.com/unikkye.showPubli